-- Seam smoke: proves the self-hosted compiler renders the effects body.
-- The smoke runner asserts the emitted .smt2 contains BOTH
-- `(declare-fun effects` AND `(Exit 0)`; if the renderer drops the
-- constraint, both are missing and the .smt2 stops at `is_first_tick`.
-- Small on purpose — the seam takes ~3 s per emit.

import "stdlib/kernel.ev"

claim main
    effects ∈ Seq(Effect) = ⟨Exit(0)⟩
